        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 2:04PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 202 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 20
miles northwest of Henrys Lake, moving northeast at 45 mph. In
addition to lightning and brief heavy rainfall, this storm may
produce strong wind gusts and small hail.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
West Yellowstone, Raynolds Pass, Lakeview, Yellowstone Village, and
Red Rock Pass.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
